children.subject:
I took 61b with Hilfinger past fall and he has more work - more hws and (in my opinion) harder projects (esp without project partners). 

Unless you expect to be a whiz at any of the subjects, that schedule will be tough. 

You can reduce the amount of work you have to turn in by doing 70's test-only option, but you need to ensure that you can stay on top of the material and do well on the tests.

I took 16B, 61B, and 70 this semester - it's admittedly a pretty heavy schedule, but it's doable if you stay on top of everything. All three classes have assignments due weekly, so if 70 offers a test-only option, definitely choose it to reduce your weekly assignment load. I've heard that Hug's 61B is very different from Hilfinger's though so you may want to get a second opinion there.
+1. Exact same schedule (this sem and next sem) and exact same question.

history.content: Would a course schedule of CS 61B, CS 70, and EE 16A be manageable? I'm taking CS 61A and Math 54 right now, planning on going over Java/61B material over summer, and hoping that 54 reduces the amount of time I have to devote to 16A. On top of these classes I would be taking a relatively easy breadth course.
